# Reference the material library file
mtllib rope.mtl

# --- Vertices (x y z) ---
# Define the points in 3D space that make up the shape
v 0.0 0.0 0.0
v 1.0 0.0 0.0
v 1.0 1.0 0.0
v 0.0 1.0 0.0
# ... many more vertices for a cylinder ...

# --- Texture Coordinates (u v) --- (Optional but good practice)
# Maps vertices to texture space (if you were using a texture image)
vt 0.0 0.0
vt 1.0 0.0
vt 1.0 1.0
vt 0.0 1.0
# ...

# --- Vertex Normals (nx ny nz) ---
# Defines the direction light reflects off each vertex (for shading)
vn 0.0 0.0 1.0
vn 0.0 0.0 1.0
# ... many more normals ...

# --- Material Selection ---
# Use the material defined in the .mtl file
usemtl RopeMaterial

# --- Faces ---
# Defines the surfaces by connecting vertices (v), texture coords (vt), and normals (vn)
# Format: f v1/vt1/vn1 v2/vt2/vn2 v3/vt3/vn3  (for a triangle)
f 1/1/1 2/2/1 3/3/1
f 1/1/1 3/3/1 4/4/1
# ... many more faces ...